title: ONNX expand and expand_as operators
body_html:
Currently many graphs containing expand and expand_as operators fail to export to ONNX (for example, SSD model). Looking in to onnx/symbolic.py we see expand implemented as:

# There is no translation for it, but we don't want to raise an error yet
def expand(g, self, size, implicit):
    return None

I'm wondering if this is complete implementation . Also, currently expand_as not implemented at all. Any idea how do we implement these two operators for ONNX?

body:
Currently many graphs containing expand and expand_as operators fail to export to ONNX (for example, SSD model). Looking in to [onnx/symbolic.py](https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/master/torch/onnx/symbolic.py#L234) we see `expand` implemented as:

```
# There is no translation for it, but we don't want to raise an error yet
def expand(g, self, size, implicit):
    return None
```

I'm wondering if this is complete implementation . Also, currently `expand_as` not implemented at all. Any idea how do we implement these two operators for ONNX?
